536
00:39:28,396 --> 00:39:30,216
It's been several decades.

537
00:39:30,216 --> 00:39:32,496
That guy looks familiar.

538
00:39:38,476 --> 00:39:41,096
Mr. Ding, do you recognize this man?

539
00:39:41,096 --> 00:39:42,696
Yes.

540
00:39:42,696 --> 00:39:46,960
He's the guest of mine who killed that old dog.

541
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:50,236
- What was his name again? Zhang...
- Zhang Guang Hua.

542
00:39:50,236 --> 00:39:52,296
Yes. That's his name.

543
00:39:52,296 --> 00:39:54,496
Are you familiar with him?

544
00:39:56,740 --> 00:40:00,701
Well, your acquaintance should thank me.

545
00:40:00,701 --> 00:40:02,196
How so?

546
00:40:02,196 --> 00:40:04,756
Times were lean back then.

547
00:40:04,756 --> 00:40:05,836
We rarely got to have some meat.

548
00:40:05,836 --> 00:40:10,416
So he killed that old dog and stew it to give himself a boost.

549
00:40:10,416 --> 00:40:11,780
But I stopped him.

550
00:40:11,780 --> 00:40:14,980
Because that dog was too strange.

551
00:40:15,756 --> 00:40:16,836
Strange how?

552
00:40:16,836 --> 00:40:18,216
Strange how?

553
00:40:18,216 --> 00:40:21,516
It had many hairless patches on its body.

554
00:40:21,516 --> 00:40:23,956
Not the kind that shed naturally.

555
00:40:23,956 --> 00:40:26,916
It was more like someone had stuck tape on it

556
00:40:26,916 --> 00:40:28,476
and then ripped it off,

557
00:40:28,476 --> 00:40:31,076
pulling the hair out along with it.

558
00:40:31,076 --> 00:40:33,756
How many of those tape-like strips were there?

559
00:40:34,516 --> 00:40:39,756
There were three, four... They were intertwined.

560
00:40:39,756 --> 00:40:41,756
I didn't count them.

561
00:40:43,276 --> 00:40:46,656
Mr. Ding, let's go.

562
00:40:46,656 --> 00:40:51,236
Alright. Once we climb over, we'll be there.

563
00:40:51,236 --> 00:40:52,716
Let's go.

564
00:40:57,876 --> 00:40:59,296
Come on.

565
00:41:00,196 --> 00:41:03,036
Look.

566
00:41:03,036 --> 00:41:05,796
We're here. This is the tree.

567
00:41:10,216 --> 00:41:13,036
- Come on.
- Mr. Ding, thank you.

568
00:41:13,036 --> 00:41:16,836
Thanks. Don't stay too long in there.

569
00:41:16,836 --> 00:41:18,596
The weather in the mountains changes quickly.

570
00:41:18,596 --> 00:41:20,136
It can turn cold all of a sudden.

571
00:41:20,136 --> 00:41:21,676
Stay safe.

572
00:41:21,676 --> 00:41:23,516
Be careful.

573
00:41:23,516 --> 00:41:24,696
Remember.

574
00:41:24,696 --> 00:41:26,136
Be careful.

575
00:41:26,136 --> 00:41:28,516
- Careful.
- Stay sharp.

576
00:41:30,036 --> 00:41:33,436
It seems that dog was the Literate Dog.

577
00:41:33,436 --> 00:41:36,576
It got lost in the mountains and by chance,

578
00:41:36,576 --> 00:41:37,916
broke the seal of the relics of ill omen,

579
00:41:37,916 --> 00:41:39,476
staying alive all this time.

580
00:41:39,476 --> 00:41:41,476
Based on past experiences, the relics of ill omen

581
00:41:41,476 --> 00:41:43,656
likely chose Zhang Guang Hua themselves.

582
00:41:43,656 --> 00:41:45,056
Otherwise, as an ordinary person,

583
00:41:45,056 --> 00:41:46,876
he couldn't have taken down that dog.

584
00:41:46,876 --> 00:41:50,256
Hard to say how many of them attached themselves to him.

585
00:41:50,256 --> 00:41:53,676
If Zhang Guang Hua had two relics of ill omen
and lost one to Liu Shu Hai

586
00:41:53,676 --> 00:41:57,316
after falling into the water,
then he'd have one left.

587
00:41:57,316 --> 00:41:59,796
In that case, he might still be alive.

588
00:42:00,836 --> 00:42:03,116
If he still has the relic of ill omen within him,

589
00:42:03,116 --> 00:42:05,556
